					<span>Chapter 0: Installation</span>
					<div>“Set Up Wordpress and your Nightsprout Theme”</div>
				</h3>
				<p>Before you install a Nightsprout theme, you have to have a working WordPress install.  Anything that we write here will probably pale in comparison to the existing WordPress Documentation.  <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Getting_Started_with_WordPress">Click here to give it a read.</a></p>
				<p>Once you have that set up, getting Empire on your system is relatively easy.  You have a few options, but we suggest this way for most users:</p>
				<ul>
				  <li>Via the WordPress Admin Panel
				    <ol>
				      <li>Log in to WordPress as the admin user.</li>
				      <li>Click on the "Appearance" menu item, and then the "Themes" sub-menu item inside of it.</li>
				      <li>Click on the "Install Themes", and then the "Upload" sub-tab below it.</li>
				      <li>Click on the "Choose File" button and browse to the location of the theme's zip file.</li>
				      <li>Select the file, and click "Install Now".</li>
				    </ol>
				  </li>
				</ul>
				<p>If this doesn't work for you, there are other common methods to install a theme <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Using_Themes">well documented here on the WordPress Documentation site.</a> If you have any problems installing your theme, feel free to <a href="http://cssframework.heroku.com/themedoc/home#">contact our customer support</a>.</p>
