					<span>Chapter 1: Configuring Your Front Page</span>
					<div>“Start Rocking Your New Theme”</div>
				</h3>
				<p>To get started, lets configure your front page.  If you don't want to use your Nightsprout Front Page, skip to Chapter 2, which details what to do to deactivate it or otherwise make it not the main page of your site.</p>
				<p>Inside of the WordPress Admin interface, click on the "Empire Config" option in the main menu.  It should be one of the first options.  This will take you to Nightsprout's custom theme administration panel.  The first page you see is the Front Page Settings area, where you can customize the look of the Nightsprout Front Page.</p>
				<p>The first set of options is the <em>Banner Gallery</em>.  Here, you can specify which images you want to use for the rotating front page image gallery.  Inside of each text box, you need to input the full URL address for the images you want to post (or the relative ones if you're an advanced user and have the correct relative path).  To the right of each of the URL text inputs, we've placed buttons that will open the default WordPress Media Uploader.  Here you can upload your own images, or browse the images that you've already uploaded yourself.</p>
				<p><b>NOTE:</b> you can NOT use the "Insert into post" option, or anything similar in this instance.  You must use the Link URL, which can be found by clicking "Show" next to an image thumbnail, and it must be the "File URL" version of the URL, which can be obtained by clicking the "File URL" button below the "Link URL"</p>
